RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFHMIN, RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFA and RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZICOND
are only supported since Linux 6.8[1], however Scarthgap ships with kernel
version 6.6. Due to this, compilation fails on risc-v:

 8:43.20 E /yocto/scarthgap/build/tmp/work/riscv64-poky-linux/firefox/153.0/firefox-153.0/js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp:319:26: error: use of undeclared identifier 'RIS
CV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFHMIN'cd 
 8:43.20 E   319 |     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFHMIN) {
 8:43.20 E       |                          ^
 8:43.20 js/xpconnect/wrappers/XrayWrapper.o
 8:43.20 js/xpconnect/wrappers/Unified_cpp_xpconnect_wrappers0.o
 8:43.28 E /yocto/scarthgap/build/tmp/work/riscv64-poky-linux/firefox/153.0/firefox-153.0/js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp:322:26: error: use of undeclared identifier 'RIS
CV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFA'
 8:43.28 E   322 |     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFA) {
 8:43.28 E       |                          ^
 8:43.37 E /yocto/scarthgap/build/tmp/work/riscv64-poky-linux/firefox/153.0/firefox-153.0/js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp:325:26: error: use of undeclared identifier 'RIS
CV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZICOND'
 8:43.37 E   325 |     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZICOND) {
 8:43.37 E    

Make these probes optional, guard them with an ifdef.

[1]: https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/bf4cd84111c61 and
     https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/dc6ccb21f42ce and
     https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/3359866b40a97

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [oe-specific]
Signed-off-by: Gyorgy Sarvari <skandigraun@gmail.com>

diff --git a/./js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp.orig b/./js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp
index 06c73e3..3ac9804 100644
--- a/./js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp.orig
+++ b/./js/src/jit/riscv64/Architecture-riscv64.cpp
@@ -316,15 +316,21 @@ static RVExtensions ComputeRVExtensions() {
     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZBS) {
       extensions += RVExtension::Zbs;
     }
+#ifdef RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFHMIN
     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFHMIN) {
       extensions += RVExtension::Zfhmin;
     }
+#endif
+#ifdef RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFA
     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZFA) {
       extensions += RVExtension::Zfa;
     }
+#endif
+#ifdef RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZICOND
     if (probe[0].value & RISCV_HWPROBE_EXT_ZICOND) {
       extensions += RVExtension::Zicond;
     }
+#endif
   }
 #endif
 
